Each directory contains the associated source code files that are in Operating Systems
Concepts - Seventh Edition.

In this situation where there are multiple files in a directory, please consult the 
README file for information about which file corresponds to which figure in the text.

The program files may compile with:

Java programs - javac  - available at www.javasoft.com

POSIX programs - gcc - available for most UNIX-style platforms including Linux, Solaris,
FreeBSD, and Mac OS X.

Win32 programs - There are sevral compilers available for Win32 programming. The 
Microsoft Developer Studio provides a C compiler that will compile these programs.
A good freeware compiler I have had luck with is lcc-Win32 available from

http://www.cs.virginia.edu/~lcc-win32/

Greg Gagne
